args:
The party embarks on a deep-sea voyage
aboard the remodeled Gran Fiore. But when a
giant sea creature attacks, Mym and Alex are
thrown overboard. The pair later wake up,
surprised that they yet draw breath, in the
hidden Kingdom of the Deep, Aquaphos.
{player_name} and his friends sat\nenjoying a well-earned holiday from their travails.
I'm glad everyone looks like they're\nenjoying themselves.
Yep! So let's you and I have some fun, too!
I picked out this swimsuit just for you,\nby the way. Hee hee. How's it ＂suit＂ me?
Oh, er... I think it looks lovely on you.
SQUEEE! You feel free to go right ahead\nand lock those baby blues on me as hard\nas you want, 'kay?! Me and ooonly me!

Evidently, right around here, deep at the
bottom of the sea, lie deposits of ore that
contain the mana of the ocean itself.
They're collectively called ＂tidal tears.＂
Ooh, how romantic.\nI'm tearing up just thinking about it!
I'm sure you are. Purportedly, long ago,\nan island floated here called Aquaphos.
And those who lived upon it used the mana\nwithin the tidal tears to build a culture and\ntechnology that were entirely their own.
Namely, the means by which people could\nlive in the briny deep.
IN the ocean? But how would they do that?\nHuman lungs require air, last I checked.

I couldn't tell you. Unfortunately, Aquaphos
sank beneath the waves at some point
during the First War of Binding a thousand
years ago.
But I'm sure that its people are still out\nthere, somewhere. Hee hee. Doesn't it\nabsolutely tickle your sense of adventure?
And on that note, we're off.
Hello? Adventure. In the ocean deep.\nDo try to keep up, Brother.
Wanna explain why you've got us\nall here on the Gran Fiore?

What he said. I mean, I'm totally down
with the whole deep-sea exploration thing,
but I'm pretty sure dogpaddling isn't gonna
get us far!
I'm well-prepared for that, I assure you.\nGran Fiore, time to set off!
Set off?! We're facing nothin' but ocean!
Eeeeek! We're gonna plunge into the sea!\nWe're gonna sink! WE'LL DROOOOOWN!
Not just fine—we're cruisin' right under\nthe water! How the heck?
OHO HO! That, my dears, is thanks to\nthe Gran Fiore in its Sirena Mode!
Daaaang. I can see fish swimming outside\nthe window!
Wooow! Go, Gran Fiore, go!\nWe're getting deeper by the second!
Once we reach the seafloor, we'll start our\nsurvey. The tidal tears and the secrets of\nthe lost island of Aquaphos will be mine!
That means we've gone so deep that the\nlight of the sun can no longer reach us.\nI believe we've about arrived.
Something large is attacking us! Turn the\nrudder, and get us moving in a different\ndirection, quickly!
We're out of options.\nWe have to abandon ship.
You mean leave the Gran Fiore?!
It is the quality of a true monarch to be\nable to make necessary sacrifices as\nsituations dictate.
Now then, everyone! We must hurry\nand evacuate. We'll meet on dry land.
What, are we supposed to just figure\nout the in-between stuff ourselves?!
Once we're outta the ship, we're still in\nthe pitch-dark sea with a MONSTER!\nAre we gonna make it?!
In any case, we die if we stay here!
Alex is right! Come on, everyone,\nlet's get out of here!
I shall protect you, my darling.\nStay close to me!
Guess we made it out somehow.\nHead count, team. We all here?
I haven't seen Mym, either.\nDon't tell me they're still in the water...!
(I hope the others are okay.\nGotta find them, fast...)
This is no time to be napping. Up, now!
Eeek! Come oooon, I was just getting to\nthe best part—ack! Alex?! Where are we?
I don't know, but it sure doesn't look like\nthe bottom of the ocean. There's light,\nand we can breathe.
Did we wash up on some island\nsomewhere, perhaps?
I'm Tiana! You two came from the\nsurface, right?
Deep in the ocean. Where we are now.
Are you telling me we're dead?!\nBodies consigned to a watery grave?!
Calm down. Have a look out the window.

This is the Kingdom of the Deep,
Aquaphos—home of the sea-dwelling
abyssians. Welcome, guests from the
surface.
Honestly, I'm pretty confused...\nbut you all saved us, right?
We did. You were attacked by the\nKeeper of the Seas.
The very same. It has a volatile temper,\nand will rend anything that enters its\nterritory to pieces.
Meaning it's basically a miracle we\nmade it out alive.
The fish told me of you.\nAnd so I hurried to your rescue.
Surface-dwellers really can't enter the\nKingdom, but you would have died\nhad we not intervened, so along we came.
Seems we've really put you out.\nI thank you again for your help.
Aquaphos is the island that sunk into the\nsea a thousand years ago, right? I don't\nsee any humans around, though.
Our ancestors were humans. We evolved\nto better adapt to life in the sea, and are\nnow called abyssians.
It's been a thousand years since we've\ninteracted with the surface world. Now we\nenjoy a unique and prosperous culture.
The abyssians are on the verge of\nextinction.

Though on its face this city looks to be
thriving, we've been contending with a
shortage of food and resources for some
time.
We may finally be at our limit. And lately,\nsome of our citizens have moved that we\ninvade the surface world.
Part of it is because of this city's history.\nThere are many who do not think highly of\nsurface people.

And lately, the idea has started to spread
faster. I brought you here, but I think it
would be dangerous for you to make a
move.
We can't well just stay here forever.
Yeah. I want to get home.
Perhaps YOU would be able to...\nYou are a dragon, right?
There's something I'd like you to help me\nwith. If all goes well, we might be able to\nsave us from the threat of collapse.
And if we succeed, then I could safely get\nyou back to the surface.
What do you need us to do, then?
My peers and I want to tread a path that\ninvolves neither our destruction nor\nsurface aggression.
And by that, I mean I want to create an\nobject called the Abyssal Bell and awaken\nthe god of the sea, Leviathan.
What? The only Leviathan I know of is a\nharbinger of calamity.
He is nothing of the sort!\nLeviathan is the god of the ocean,\nand the one that we abyssians worship.
Huh. Seems he has a different reputation\ndown here.
I am certain that great Leviathan could\ndeliver us from this moment of crisis.

Speaking from a dragon's point of view,
I think you might be putting a liiittle too
much faith in the idea of Leviathan solving
all your problems.
Nonetheless, if the situation has gotten\nthis bad, they may be out of alternatives.
Fair enough. I'm game for whatever gets\nme back to my darling the fastest!
So, how do we help you make one of these\nAbyssal Bells?
The bell calls for tidal tears, which can\nonly be harvested on the outskirts of the\ncity from a deep-sea volcano.
We abyssians can't even go near them\nbecause they get too hot, but a dragon\nlike you...
Oh, right, Chelle mentioned tidal tears.\nThey're some kind of special mineral.
A little volcanic vacay? I'm your gal!\nThis'll be a piece of cake.
Thank you. Let's get the Abyssal Bell\nmade and then awaken Leviathan!
